h3.Steps to Reproduce
# Download the attached test.csv
# Login to JIRA, create a new Project with a project key = "WOR"
# Navigate to {{JIRA Administration >> Import Export >> External System Import >> CSV Import}}
# Import the attached test.csv, and map the values as per the screenshot below:
!jiracsvmapping.jpg!
# After the import is complete, navigate to the issue (WOR-23), and notice that the total time logged is only 15 minutes (when it's supposed to be more than a few hours):
!jiracsvmapping2.jpg!

h3.Cause
The import does not accumulate the total logged time into this column in JIRA's database:
{code}
SELECT TIMESPENT FROM jiraissue WHERE pkey = 'WOR-23';
{code}
Notice that it only outputs 900.

Running this query instead, shows that the time logging is accurately added to the issue, but the total time spent are not accumulated:

{code}
SELECT w.ID, w.author, w.worklogbody, w.CREATED, w.STARTDATE, w.timeworked FROM worklog w JOIN jiraissue j ON w.issueid = j.id WHERE pkey = 'WOR-23';
{code}

h3.Workaround
Update the TIMESPENT column in the jiraissue table manually with the data from the output of this query:
{code}
SELECT SUM(w.timeworked) FROM worklog w JOIN jiraissue j ON w.issueid = j.id WHERE pkey = '<issueid>';
{code}

